public class Key<R extends GrammarRule<T>,T extends Token>
extends java.lang.Object

Stores information about an item that has already been proven to be a complete parse. This class will be hashed by the Chart millions of times, so an efficient hashCode() and equals(Object) method is essential. This class is also where the ambiguity unpacking occurs when final parses are being formatted.

Author:
jon
